Adjust rack to middle position (middle and top positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating
whites from greens. Trim @green beans{6%oz} if necessary.

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @hoisin sauce{2%tbsp}, 
@garlic powder{1%tsp}, and @water{1%tbsp}. (You'll use more garlic powder later.)
Microwave until warmed through, ~{30%seconds}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in a small #pot{} over medium-high heat.
Add scallion whites; cook until softened, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}.
Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender,
~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all
over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add beef; sear, 
turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-8%minutes}. Transfer beef to
one side of a #baking sheet{}. (For 4 servings, spread beef out across entire 
sheet.)

> For easy cleanup, line baking sheet with foil first.

> Swap in chicken or pork for beef. Cook chicken until browned and cooked
> through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook pork to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes
> per side. Add half the hoisin glaze to pan; turn chicken or pork to coat.
> Transfer to a cutting board (no need to roast!).

On opposite side of sheet from beef, toss green beans with a drizzle of oil, 
salt, and pepper. (For 4 servings, add green beans to a second baking sheet; 
roast on top rack.)

Roast on middle rack until beef is cooked through and green beans are tender,
~{10-12%minutes}.

In the last 3-5 minutes, remove sheet from oven; carefully pour half the hoisin
glaze (save the rest for serving) over beef, turning to coat. Return to oven 
until glaze is tacky. Transfer beef to a #cutting board{}. Let rest at least
~{5%minutes}.

> Toss and roast green beans as instructed. (Skip roasting chicken or pork.)

Meanwhile, in a second small #bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, remaining
@garlic powder{} to taste, and as much @sriracha{1%tsp} as you like. Stir in 
@water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Thinly slice beef crosswise.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} and season with salt and pepper.
Toss green beans with @ponzu sauce{6%ml} and half the @sesame seeds{1%tbsp}.

Divide rice, green beans, and beef between plates. Drizzle beef with remaining
hoisin glaze; drizzle everything with as much sriracha mayo as you like. Top with
scallion greens and as many remaining sesame seeds as you like. Serve.

> Thinly slice chicken or pork against the grain.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.